-- Sebastian Vettel Wins Singapore Grand Prix; Jenson Button Second
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2012-09-23T14:09:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-23/sebastian-vettel-wins-singapore-grand-prix-jenson-button-second.html
Sebastian Vettel of Red Bull won
today’s Singapore Grand Prix to move up to second in the Formula
One drivers’ standings.  Jenson Button of McLaren came second and Ferrari’s Fernando
Alonso was third in the floodlit night race on the Marina Bay
street circuit. McLaren’s  Lewis Hamilton  retired from the race
with a mechanical problem.  Alonso retains the lead in the drivers’ standings.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  